    <line x1="516.6666666666667" y1="80" x2="516.6666666666667" y2="200" 
          class="connection-line" marker-end="url(#arrow)"/>
    <text x="516.6666666666667" y="135.0" text-anchor="middle" 
          class="node-text" font-size="12">&gt; C[Run Installer with sudo] C </text>
    <line x1="516.6666666666667" y1="200" x2="516.6666666666667" y2="320" 
          class="connection-line" marker-end="url(#arrow)"/>
    <text x="516.6666666666667" y="255.0" text-anchor="middle" 
          class="node-text" font-size="12">&gt; E[Choose Installation Directory] E </text>
    <rect x="217.33333333333337" y="55" width="132" height="50" 
          rx="5" class="node-rect"/>
    <text x="283.33333333333337" y="80" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="middle" 
          class="node-text">Download XAMPP</text>
    <rect x="406.66666666666674" y="55" width="220" height="50" 
          rx="5" class="node-rect"/>
    <text x="516.6666666666667" y="80" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="middle" 
          class="node-text">Make Installer Executable</text>
    <rect x="181.33333333333337" y="175" width="204" height="50" 
          rx="5" class="node-rect"/>
    <text x="283.33333333333337" y="200" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="middle" 
          class="node-text">Run Installer with sudo</text>
    <rect x="438.66666666666674" y="175" width="156" height="50" 
          rx="5" class="node-rect"/>
    <text x="516.6666666666667" y="200" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="middle" 
          class="node-text">Select Components</text>
    <rect x="157.33333333333337" y="295" width="252" height="50" 
          rx="5" class="node-rect"/>
    <text x="283.33333333333337" y="320" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="middle" 
          class="node-text">Choose Installation Directory</text>
    <rect x="422.66666666666674" y="295" width="188" height="50" 
          rx="5" class="node-rect"/>
    <text x="516.6666666666667" y="320" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="middle" 
          class="node-text">Complete Installation</text>
    <rect x="286.0" y="415" width="228" height="50" 
          rx="5" class="node-rect"/>
    <text x="400.0" y="440" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="middle" 
          class="node-text">Launch XAMPP Control Panel</text>
</svg>
</div>
            
            <h3>Step 4: Starting XAMPP</h3>
            <p>You can start XAMPP in two ways:</p>
            
            <h4>Using the Control Panel</h4>
            <pre><code>sudo /opt/lampp/manager-linux-x64.run</code></pre>
            
            <p>This launches the graphical XAMPP control panel where you can start/stop services.</p>
            
            <h4>Using the Command Line</h4>
            <pre><code>sudo /opt/lampp/lampp start</code></pre>
            
            <p>This starts all XAMPP services (Apache, MySQL, etc.) at once. You can also use:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><code>sudo /opt/lampp/lampp stop</code> - Stop all services</li>
                <li><code>sudo /opt/lampp/lampp restart</code> - Restart all services</li>
                <li><code>sudo /opt/lampp/lampp status</code> - Check the status of services</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>Step 5: Verifying the Installation</h3>
            <p>Open your web browser and navigate to <code>http://localhost</code> or <code>http://127.0.0.1</code>. You should see the XAMPP welcome page.</p>
            
            <p>To check if PHP is working correctly, create a test file:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Create a file at <code>/opt/lampp/htdocs/info.php</code> with the following content:</li>
            </ol>
            <pre><code>&lt;?php
phpinfo();
?&gt;</code></pre>
            
            <li>Navigate to <code>http://localhost/info.php</code> in your browser</li>
            <li>You should see a detailed page with PHP configuration information</li>
            
            <h3>Creating a Desktop Shortcut (Optional)</h3>
            <p>For easier access, you can create a desktop shortcut:</p>
            <pre><code>sudo nano ~/.local/share/applications/xampp-control-panel.desktop</code></pre>
            
            <p>Add the following content:</p>
            <pre><code>[Desktop Entry]
Version=1.0
Type=Application
Name=XAMPP Control Panel
Comment=Start and Stop XAMPP
Exec=sudo /opt/lampp/manager-linux-x64.run
Icon=/opt/lampp/htdocs/favicon.ico
Terminal=false
Categories=Development;Web;
Keywords=xampp;php;apache;mysql;</code></pre>
            
            <p>Save and close the file (Ctrl+O, Enter, Ctrl+X). You'll need to make it executable:</p>
            <pre><code>chmod +x ~/.local/share/applications/xampp-control-panel.desktop</code></pre>
            
            <h3>Security Considerations</h3>
            <p>By default, XAMPP is configured for convenience, not security. For a more secure setup:</p>
            <pre><code>sudo /opt/lampp/lampp security</code></pre>
            
            <p>This will launch a security wizard that helps you set passwords for MySQL, phpMyAdmin, and other components.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="individual-components">
            <h2>Installing Individual Components (LAMP Stack)</h2>
            <p>For a more Ubuntu-native approach, you can install each component individually using the package manager. This gives you more control and better integration with the system.</p>
            
            <h3>Step 1: Update System Packages</h3>
            <pre><code>sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade</code></pre>
            
            <h3>Step 2: Install Apache Web Server</h3>
            <pre><code>sudo apt install apache2</code></pre>
            
            <p>After installation, Apache should start automatically. Verify it's running:</p>
            <pre><code>sudo systemctl status apache2</code></pre>
            
            <p>You can also check by opening <code>http://localhost</code> in your browser, which should display the Apache default page.</p>
            
            <h3>Step 3: Install MySQL (or MariaDB)</h3>
            <p>You can install either MySQL or MariaDB (a community-developed fork of MySQL):</p>
            
            <h4>Option 1: MySQL</h4>
            <pre><code>sudo apt install mysql-server</code></pre>
            
            <p>Secure your MySQL installation:</p>
            <pre><code>sudo mysql_secure_installation</code></pre>
            
            <h4>Option 2: MariaDB</h4>
            <pre><code>sudo apt install mariadb-server</code></pre>
            
            <p>Secure your MariaDB installation:</p>
            <pre><code>sudo mysql_secure_installation</code></pre>
            
            <h3>Step 4: Install PHP</h3>
            <pre><code>sudo apt install php libapache2-mod-php php-mysql</code></pre>
            
            <p>This installs PHP, the Apache PHP module, and the PHP MySQL extension.</p>
            
            <h3>Step 5: Install Additional PHP Extensions</h3>
            <p>Depending on your needs, you might want to install additional PHP extensions:</p>
            <pre><code>sudo apt install php-curl php-json php-cgi php-gd php-mbstring php-xml php-xmlrpc php-zip</code></pre>
            
            <h3>Step 6: Install phpMyAdmin (Optional)</h3>
            <p>phpMyAdmin provides a web interface to manage your MySQL databases:</p>
            <pre><code>sudo apt install phpmyadmin</code></pre>
            
            <p>During installation:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Select Apache2 when prompted for the web server</li>
                <li>Choose Yes when asked to configure a database for phpMyAdmin</li>
                <li>Enter a password for the phpMyAdmin application</li>
            </ol>
            
            <h3>Step 7: Configure Apache to Prioritize PHP Files</h3>
            <p>Edit the Apache configuration file:</p>
            <pre><code>sudo nano /etc/apache2/mods-enabled/dir.conf</code></pre>
            
            <p>Move index.php to be first in the DirectoryIndex list:</p>
            <pre><code>&lt;IfModule mod_dir.c&gt;
    DirectoryIndex index.php index.html index.cgi index.pl index.xhtml index.htm
&lt;/IfModule&gt;</code></pre>
            
            <h3>Step 8: Restart Apache to Apply Changes</h3>
            <pre><code>sudo systemctl restart apache2</code></pre>
            
            <h3>Step 9: Verify PHP Installation</h3>
            <p>Create a test PHP file:</p>
            <pre><code>echo '&lt;?php phpinfo(); ?&gt;' | sudo tee /var/www/html/info.php</code></pre>
            
            <p>Open <code>http://localhost/info.php</code> in your browser to see the PHP information page.</p>
            
            <h3>Managing Services</h3>
            <p>Ubuntu uses systemd to manage services. Here are some common commands:</p>
            <pre><code># Apache
sudo systemctl start apache2    # Start Apache
sudo systemctl stop apache2     # Stop Apache
sudo systemctl restart apache2  # Restart Apache
sudo systemctl status apache2   # Check Apache status

# MySQL/MariaDB
sudo systemctl start mysql      # Start MySQL
sudo systemctl stop mysql       # Stop MySQL
sudo systemctl restart mysql    # Restart MySQL
sudo systemctl status mysql     # Check MySQL status</code></pre>
        </section>

        <section class="docker-setup">
            <h2>Setting Up Development Environment with Docker</h2>
            <p>Docker provides a modern, containerized approach to development environments. It offers the best isolation and consistency between development and production.</p>

<div class="mermaid-converted" style="margin: 1.5rem auto; padding: 1rem; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; max-width: 100%;">
<div style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 12px; color: #6c757d; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px;">Diagram
</div>
    <svg viewBox="0 0 800 500" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" 
     style="max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin: 0 auto; background: white; border-radius: 8px;; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin: 0 auto;">
    <!-- Embedded styles for this diagram only -->
    <defs>
        <style type="text/css">
            .node-rect { fill: #e1f5fe; stroke: #01579b; stroke-width: 2px; }
            .node-rect:hover { fill: #b3e5fc; }
            .node-text { fill: #01579b; font-family: 'Segoe UI', Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; }
